definition.value: A primary alcohol that is 1,3-thiazol-3-ium substituted by (4-amino-2-methylpyrimidin-5-yl)methyl, methyl and 2-hydroxyethyl groups at positions 3, 4 and 5, respectively.
A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid having the carboxy group at the 2-position.
A dicarboxylic acid anion resuting from removal of a proton from both carboxy groups of N-formimidoyl-L-aspartic acid.
A trihydroxyflavone that is flavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4', 5 and 7.  It induces autophagy in leukaemia cells.
